column21: I wrote my review on TrustPiliot. To be clear I didn't want to write this (and I tried to talk myself out of doing it), the team were lovely but the results for the amount I paid was very lacklustre.
column23: Provide a scope of work so the users know exactly what they're getting for. Agree on KPIs - what does a successful campaign look like? Include guaranteed publications up front (as a PR campaign you should have the relationships to do this and the confidence in the artist and product for it to be successful) and a range of numbers for the project to be successful. Agree to payment at the end of a campaign (like any other business) so if these KPIs are not met then this can be compensated.

My only feedback would be to maybe consider some tools like isitagoodplaylist.com for playlisting. A few of the playlist placements reached listeners that saved the song and followed me on Spotify, but some of them had a large spike in followers about 9-12 months ago that might signify that the playlists have some fake followers. These playlists got a lot of streams but almost no repeat listeners, saves, or follows.

column21: Overall, my experience working with your agency on the promotion of my debut album, "MatterMoreForSis," had both positive and challenging aspects. I appreciate the quick response and professional pitch from the A&R during the initial engagement. Settling the campaign service fees promptly demonstrated my commitment to the campaign. However, the delay in starting the campaign was concerning and led me to question the legitimacy of the service, which eroded my trust in the beginning and impacted my confidence in the campaign.   Press Nathan kept the lines of communication open, promptly responding to my queries and providing updates every Friday. His efforts secured placements in prominent publications like "Wonderland" and "Music Crowns," among other notable media outlets. Seeing my music featured on such reputable platforms was a dream come true. I believe there is still untapped potential to explore and target even broader press coverage and I look forward to future opportunities to work together and continue spreading the message of my music to an even broader audience.  Playlisting Rich's dedication to providing consistent updates on playlisting placements as promised is commendable, and I genuinely appreciate the effort put into the campaign. However, I must be honest and admit that the results of the playlisting campaign fell below my initial expectations. One area that I believe could have been improved is the timing of playlist placements. Not having my lead single, "Survive The Night," playlisted on its release day was a missed opportunity. As we know, the first day of release is when the majority of listeners pay attention to a new track, and having it featured on playlists from the get-go could have significantly boosted its visibility. Additionally, I had hoped for playlisting in Spotify editorial playlists, which unfortunately did not materialize. It's worth considering ways to strengthen our approach to securing placements in these highly influential playlists, as they can have a substantial impact on an artist's exposure. Furthermore, while there was mention of Apple Music playlist pitching during the campaign discussions, we did not receive any placements there. To ensure more comprehensive coverage in the future, exploring strategies to secure playlisting across multiple platforms, including Apple Music, would be beneficial.  To be clear, I am grateful for the effort put into the playlisting campaign, but I believe there is room for improvement. I hope that in our future collaborations, we can work together to refine the approach and achieve even better results. As an artist investing in my debut album, "MatterMoreForSis," I'm eager to explore all avenues to maximize its exposure and reach a broader audience.  Thank you once again for your hard work and dedication. I look forward to discussing ways to enhance the playlisting strategy and further promote the album's music in our future endeavors. Looking ahead, I would suggest fostering more open communication and transparency from the beginning to the end of the campaign process. Regular progress updates, transparent discussions on strategy, and timely responses to any concerns would significantly strengthen the artist-agency relationship and instill confidence in the campaign's progress. I remain enthusiastic about working with your agency and believe that, with strategic adjustments and enhanced communication, we can achieve even greater success in promoting my music.
